# p5 sandbox & export

## P5Canvas

- User/AI code runs via `new Function('p', cleanCode)` — treat as untrusted
- Strip markdown fences from AI output before eval
- Default fallback `p.setup` if AI omits it; wrap `p.draw` for runtime errors → `RUNTIME_ERR` on canvas, `noLoop()`
- Canvas 400×400; CSS `scale()` via ResizeObserver (max ~2x)
- `P5CanvasRef`: `downloadGif`, `downloadPng(filename, size?)` for cursor sizes

## exportService

- `generateExportPack({ code, platform, filename })` — platforms: `windows` | `linux` | `chrome`
- Ghost p5 instance; mock `p.millis()` for frame sequence; JSZip + file-saver
- **Not called from App UI yet** — wiring belongs in App/Terminal with `exportState` progress

## Safety

- No external p5 libraries in generated code
- Prefer fixing sanitization over disabling sandbox for demos
